電子全文



研究生中文姓名:林束敏研究生英文姓名:Lin, Shu-Min中文論文名稱:原住民地區休閒農業結合文化創意產業發展策略之研究-以屏東縣為例英文論文名稱:Study on the Development of Leisure Agriculture Integrated with the Cultural Creative Industries in the Indigenous Region- Taking Pintung County as an Example指導教授姓名:指導教授︰段兆麟學位類別:碩士校院名稱:屏東科技大學系所名稱:農企業管理系所學號:N9850004畢業年度:100畢業學年度:99學期:二語文別:中文論文頁數:156中文關鍵詞:原住民地區、休閒農業、文化創意產業、發展策略英文關鍵字:indigenous areas、leisure agriculture、cultural and creative industries、development strategies相關次數:

推薦:0點閱:445評分:下載:59收藏:0



農業未來發展趨勢將涵蓋生態保育、環境保護、文化、糧食安全與休閒農業。政府農業政策以「休閒農業」為施政重點。「行政院原住民族委原會」積極輔導原住民改善經濟、教育與傳統技藝維護；休閒旅遊活動也掀起對原住民文化探索熱潮。原住民地區休閒農業發展結合文化創意產業；不僅可以建立休閒農業特色，且能保存原住民文化與繁榮部落經濟。因此本研究以SWOT分析為研究基礎，透過與業者、學者的深度訪談方式，分析原住民地區休閒農業結合文化創意產業發展資源與可行性，探討產、官、學界對休閒農業結合文化創意產業發展策略之建議，並針對問題提出具體可行之策略，作為業者與政府施政參考。本研究結果顯示：原住民地區休閒農業資源豐富且生態多樣化，以自然農法耕種並作有機認證，可獲取較高的經濟利益。原住民文化特色鮮明，在產品包裝設計與行銷上，以文化圖騰Logo建立品牌形象，可增加辦識度與知名度。休閒農業結合文化創意產業，資源整體規劃發展具可行性。農業體驗活動加入原住民傳統文化元素，朝向創意開發與多元發展，有利於提昇產業競爭力與市場區隔。行銷管理與解說服務提供導覽手冊與深度解說，可加深遊客對原住民地區休閒農業旅遊認知與聯想。本文建議：（一）政府部門方面：應加強環境維護、景點設置與科技資訊服務，定期舉辦大型活動塑造形象與提升知名度。培育創意設計人才及協助輔導有潛力的產業營造指標性效果。（二）業者部份方面：以優勢資源發展有機農業與綠色生態，營造休閒農業旅遊特色。依不同季節配合祭典活動設計農業結合文化的體驗活動。經營者在整體行銷與創意開發策略要有創新之規劃，掌握農場遊客的消費行為，強調顧客服務提供深度休閒農業旅遊。

In consideration to the future trends of agricultural development, the scope covers ecological conservation, environmental protection, culture, agricultural food security, and leisure agriculture. In regards to the government’s agriculture related policies, “the leisure industry” shall remain the policy focus. The “Council of Indigenous People, Executive Yuan” has actively provided counseling to indigenous people to help them improve their financial situations and education and preserve the traditional skills. The recreational tourism activities have also set off a wave of aboriginal culture exploration. The leisure agriculture development in indigenous areas combined with the cultural creativity industry have not only contributed to the establishment of the leisure agriculture features, but have also helped conserve the indigenous culture and have promoted tribal economic prosperity. Therefore, with the SWOT analysis as the research basis and through in-depth interviews with operators and scholars, the study analyzes resources and feasibility of leisure agriculture, combined with cultural creativity industry development; the study also explores suggestions proposed by the government, academia and industry sectors on leisure agriculture, coupled with the cultural creativity industry development. The problem-specific and feasible strategies were then proposed to serve as a reference for the operators and government during policy implementation.The results show that the recreational farms in indigenous areas boast abundant agricultural resources and ecological diversity. With the natural farming method and organic farming certification, higher economic benefits can be obtained. As the indigenous culture possess distinctive features, in terms of product packaging design and marketing, the cultural totem LOGO was adopted to build the brand image and enhance the degree of identity and brand awareness. In leisure agriculture, coupled with the cultural and creative industries, the overall resource planning and development have been proven feasible. The inclusion of traditional indigenous cultural elements in agricultural experiential activities and the creativity-based and diverse developments will help enhance the industrial competitiveness and market segmentation. In terms of marketing management and illustration services, guide manuals and in-depth interpretations are provided to deepen visitors’ perception and association of the leisure and agricultural tourism in indigenous areas.In this paper, it is suggested that: (1) Government sector: to strengthen environmental maintenance, set up tourist attractions, offer technology information services, regularly organize large activities to shape the image and enhance the awareness; to foster talents in creative design and assist in offering guidance to industries with potentials in order to create indicatory results; (2) Operators in the industry: To develop organic agriculture and green ecologies through the advantageous resources in order to create the tourist attractions of leisure farms. Agricultural and cultural experimental activities were designed in consideration to the seasons, coupled with the festivals. The operators engaged in innovative planning of the overall marketing and creative development strategies in order to gain an insight into the farm visitors’ consumption behaviors, thus giving emphasis to customer service and providing comprehensive leisure agricultural tourism.

